title: Tour de Scottsdale
description: Annual charity bike ride consisting of 30 mile and 70 mile courses.
course: 30 mile and 70 mile courses. The 30 mile ride in partially supported by police for the exception of the last 8 miles. The 70 mile course is completely supported by police. There are 6 aid/water stations along the course, course marshals, HAM radio volunteers, as well as 6 mobile SAG vehicles.
registration:
Registration is online through Chronotrack; https://register.chronotrack.com/r/28477
USAC waivers will be signed and are required at packet pick up to received timing chip and shirt.
notes: The Tour de Scottsdale is not a race, but a ride. It is timed for tracking purposes, however there are no prizes or purse available.
directions: Start and Finish are located at 20825 N. Pima Road. Scottsdale, AZ 85255

description: Ninja Mountain Bike Performance Skills Event
course:
JOIN US FOR A CHALLENGING AND FUN 2-DAY CAMP ON THE BEST TERRAIN SEDONA HAS TO OFFER.

Its time to take your skills to a whole new level.
This camp is designed for the enthusiast rider or avid racer that is looking to build up and clean up their toolbox of mountain bike skills in order to handle a variety of terrain at speed.

We will blend an in-depth version of our traditional Intermediate / Advanced skills training with coached riding sessions.
